&amp; Suzanne van den Berk</p><p></p><p><i>We share our experiences, positive effects, teach about  specific veggies &amp; edible plants and do a tasting. Max 15  participants.\\u00a0</i></p>\"}, \"id\": \"3492c05e-029e-4ed6-8b91-e68024ffe9bd\", \"type\": \"paragraph_block\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p><b>Evening Anniversary Celebration</b></p><p></p><p>17.00 - 17.30 Walk in\\u00a0</p><p></p><p>17.30 - 19.00 Inspiring stories looking back and into the future</p><p>                       Book launch: Symbiosis in Development (SiD)</p><p>                       Launch of the Except Sustainability Academy</p><p>                       Performance by the ALMA Quartet</p><p></p><p>19.00 - 21.00 Dinner by Instock\\u00a0</p><p></p><p>21.00 - 23.00 DJs and Dance\\u00a0</p>\"}, \"id\": \"a46db86c-5305-4248-a7bc-5affa5c8aee6\", \"type\": \"paragraph_block\"}, {\"value\": {\"size\": \"h3\", \"heading_text\": \"Registration\"}, \"id\": \"ce2ea541-ec38-4881-963b-bbbc562f639a\", \"type\": \"heading_block\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p> Please register for parts of the program via <a href=\\\"https://forms.gle/MG3XQXLKZBhsiXeW7\\\"><b>this link</b></a>.<br/></p><p>For any questions, contact Saskia (saskia@except.nl). <br/>Follow our <a href=\\\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/except---integrated-sustainability/\\\">LinkedIn</a> and <a href=\\\"https://twitter.com/home\\\">Twitter</a> for our highlighted projects and further announcements.\\u00a0 </p>\"}, \"id\": \"8646149d-b92a-45b0-a53f-1e1d125ef7df\", \"type\": \"paragraph_block\"}]','[]',NULL,NULL),(37,1,'Except Academy Launches at Duurzame Week','Except Academy Launches at Duurzame Week',NULL,'With an intimate session on integrated sustainability','With an intimate session on integrated sustainability',NULL,'2019-06-20','During this years Duurzame Week, Except Integrated Sustainability launches the Except Academy. The  Except Academy guides individuals and teams, and gives them the tools and tenacity to realise actionable pathways towards long term sustainable organisations, cities, products, and industries. Except Academy was created to increase  sustainability literacy and leadership capacity; what\'s needed to help build a sustainable society.','During this years Duurzame Week, Except Integrated Sustainability launches the Except Academy. The  Except Academy guides individuals and teams, and gives them the tools and tenacity to realise actionable pathways towards long term sustainable organisations, cities, products, and industries. Except Academy was created to increase  sustainability literacy and leadership capacity; what\'s needed to help build a sustainable society.','',NULL,'AR',1,1,'[{\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>In partnership with the Duurzame Week, we opened our doors on Monday  17th of June to a small group of local sustainability enthusiasts. In  the session, we asked the question &quot;how can you create systemic  sustainable impact?&quot;</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"f95c3e61-4420-4d54-b329-37b8c3c7eb9f\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>During the intimate session on integrated sustainability Freek van der  Pluijm, Except&#x27;s Facilitator for Organizational Change, challenged  participants to zoom out from the object level and start looking at the  network and the system lying beyond.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"370ee78e-700a-4f91-886b-ffef007533d5\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>\\u201cWhen working with sustainability we very often tend to zoom in on a  small part \\u2013 a minute element \\u2013 of a bigger system: how can we make this  item, say plastic bottle, sustainable?&quot; asks Freek.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"013026c2-7b23-43d1-8187-e0bae08daf7d\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>&quot;When we approach the same question in a slightly different way \\u2013 by  asking \\u201chow can our processes of designing, producing, using, and  disposing off this plastic bottle better contribute to the transition  toward a more sustainable society?\\u201d all of a sudden a myriad of  opportunities start to present themselves,&quot; says Freek. &quot;And it is here  when we can start creating value by using an integrated perspective to  sustainability.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"1d0eb620-dd0d-4480-b8b6-570533886c1e\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 43, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"84f94366-d3c5-4eaf-ad10-ec4984c30362\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>\\u201cYesterday&#x27;s session was about taking a step back: we walked through the  three layers of systems thinking \\u2013 the object, network and systems  level \\u2013 and began looking at how to leverage each. This is the crucial  step of systems thinking and takes time to sink in, but just by having  the conversation, we are making vital steps towards building the  foundations of a more sustainable society,&quot; he continues.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"ba317d9e-1632-46fb-8792-ca7ed762c57b\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Systems thinking unravels the complexity of sustainability, realizing  short-term results, and long term positive impacts. Symbiosis in  Development (SiD) is Except&#x27;s framework for integrated sustainable  development. SiD allows individuals and multidisciplinary teams to  develop actionable pathways towards long term sustainable organizations,  cities, products, and industry.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"95bc582d-04b1-4000-ba15-97c47bfe76b0\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>\\u201cIt was a true pleasure to work with such a diverse and motivated group  of people, all bringing their unique and valuable perspectives to the  table on how they themselves can make their meaningful contribution,&quot;  Freek concludes.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"6a170c89-1adb-4c68-b7a9-f9fcc6f5c969\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>The Except Academy offers various courses for professionals that want to  dive deeper into sustainability. This includes a half day orientation  course, three day intensive courses, half year training trajectories,  and custom in-company training programs.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"99bdec79-c19a-4d8e-a463-835788420954\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 44, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"b4588598-d14d-4ad9-916e-a7a26bb6948b\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"About Except Academy\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"138a2f8c-dd3b-450a-98c3-0c07a675f661\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>For the past twenty years, Except has worked on the open source  \\u00a0Symbiosis in Development (SiD) framework for integrated sustainability  and applied this in business, government and research. \\u00a0The Except  Academy offers courses in systemic, integrated sustainability. This  means that we focus on long term societal transition, as a means to  reach a society that is sustainable in an environmental, social,  physical, and economic sense. This is applicable for people wanting to  make a fundamental change in how companies, governments, and industry  functions.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"de137b79-4978-44f3-a458-c38f1a829968\"}]','[{\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>In partnership with the Duurzame Week, we opened our doors on Monday  17th of June to a small group of local sustainability enthusiasts. In  the session, we asked the question &quot;how can you create systemic  sustainable impact?&quot;</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"f95c3e61-4420-4d54-b329-37b8c3c7eb9f\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>During the intimate session on integrated sustainability Freek van der  Pluijm, Except&#x27;s Facilitator for Organizational Change, challenged  participants to zoom out from the object level and start looking at the  network and the system lying beyond.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"370ee78e-700a-4f91-886b-ffef007533d5\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>\\u201cWhen working with sustainability we very often tend to zoom in on a  small part \\u2013 a minute element \\u2013 of a bigger system: how can we make this  item, say plastic bottle, sustainable?&quot; asks Freek.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"013026c2-7b23-43d1-8187-e0bae08daf7d\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>&quot;When we approach the same question in a slightly different way \\u2013 by  asking \\u201chow can our processes of designing, producing, using, and  disposing off this plastic bottle better contribute to the transition  toward a more sustainable society?\\u201d all of a sudden a myriad of  opportunities start to present themselves,&quot; says Freek. &quot;And it is here  when we can start creating value by using an integrated perspective to  sustainability.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"1d0eb620-dd0d-4480-b8b6-570533886c1e\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 43, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"84f94366-d3c5-4eaf-ad10-ec4984c30362\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>\\u201cYesterday&#x27;s session was about taking a step back: we walked through the  three layers of systems thinking \\u2013 the object, network and systems  level \\u2013 and began looking at how to leverage each. This is the crucial  step of systems thinking and takes time to sink in, but just by having  the conversation, we are making vital steps towards building the  foundations of a more sustainable society,&quot; he continues.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"ba317d9e-1632-46fb-8792-ca7ed762c57b\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Systems thinking unravels the complexity of sustainability, realizing  short-term results, and long term positive impacts. Symbiosis in  Development (SiD) is Except&#x27;s framework for integrated sustainable  development. SiD allows individuals and multidisciplinary teams to  develop actionable pathways towards long term sustainable organizations,  cities, products, and industry.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"95bc582d-04b1-4000-ba15-97c47bfe76b0\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>\\u201cIt was a true pleasure to work with such a diverse and motivated group  of people, all bringing their unique and valuable perspectives to the  table on how they themselves can make their meaningful contribution,&quot;  Freek concludes.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"6a170c89-1adb-4c68-b7a9-f9fcc6f5c969\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>The Except Academy offers various courses for professionals that want to  dive deeper into sustainability. This includes a half day orientation  course, three day intensive courses, half year training trajectories,  and custom in-company training programs.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"99bdec79-c19a-4d8e-a463-835788420954\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 44, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"b4588598-d14d-4ad9-916e-a7a26bb6948b\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"About Except Academy\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"138a2f8c-dd3b-450a-98c3-0c07a675f661\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>For the past twenty years, Except has worked on the open source  \\u00a0Symbiosis in Development (SiD) framework for integrated sustainability  and applied this in business, government and research. \\u00a0The Except  Academy offers courses in systemic, integrated sustainability. This  means that we focus on long term societal transition, as a means to  reach a society that is sustainable in an environmental, social,  physical, and economic sense. This is applicable for people wanting to  make a fundamental change in how companies, governments, and industry  functions.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"de137b79-4978-44f3-a458-c38f1a829968\"}]','[]',NULL,NULL);
