INSERT INTO `projects_projectpage` VALUES (33,1,'Serenity Farms','Serenity Farms',NULL,'Sustainable food production in arid regions','Sustainable food production in arid regions',NULL,'2018-10-16','Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates.','Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates.',NULL,'Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates. The core of Serenity Farms is a repeatable stamp design, producing the annual fresh food nutrition needs for over 60.000 people. It sources and treats water from renewable sources exclusively such as seawater, and is fully powered by the sun. This way we produce healthy, consistent, high quality fresh produce for people that currently have no direct food source, and greatly reduce the food\'s carbon footprint.','Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates. The core of Serenity Farms is a repeatable stamp design, producing the annual fresh food nutrition needs for over 60.000 people. It sources and treats water from renewable sources exclusively such as seawater, and is fully powered by the sun. This way we produce healthy, consistent, high quality fresh produce for people that currently have no direct food source, and greatly reduce the food\'s carbon footprint.','',1,1,'[{\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Serenity Farms produces and delivers food in regions that have limited  or no access to fresh produce. These regions currently import food,  usually through air freight, which has a large environmental impact,  reduces quality and availability, and creates inconsistent supply. For  example, in Saudi Arabia, where we are looking to develop a Serenity  Farm, over 80% of all fresh food is imported. </p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"00f89ee7-36e2-4c63-a096-bf60766e45ae\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 30, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"389ad0f5-a760-4c12-9661-d694f485250b\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"Food for the desert\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"6c795431-31c3-4279-ab8e-3aafcc714055\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Humanity faces a global challenge of feeding 9 billion people  sustainably in 2050.\\u00a0 It is estimated that in today\\u2019s world nearly 1  billion people are malnourished. </p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"63e8d972-f243-489c-a86f-e564bf4d4b10\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"Taking into account a growing population and shifting diets, the world will need to produce 69% more food calories in 2050 than we did in 2006.\", \"attribute_name\": \"World Resources Institute\"}, \"type\": \"block_quote\", \"id\": \"22b3b799-682d-4e9b-869b-c5043e20cc60\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>A changing climate, on top of dwindling resources needed for  agriculture, complicates our collective mandate to grow more food in  time. Food security and effects on national autonomy are of significant  concern to many countries, especially those with a low domestic food  production capacity. This is especially true for arid regions, where  often no fresh produce source is available at all. To make local  sustainable food production in the desert a reality,\\u00a0 we initiated the  Serenity Farms project.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"243ee737-203e-45ae-b70a-f1763fcc3ffd\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"The ultimate goal of farming is not the growing of crops, but the cultivation and perfection of human beings.\", \"attribute_name\": \"Masanobu Fukuoka, The One-Straw Revolution\"}, \"type\": \"block_quote\", \"id\": \"e8c5bee9-e99c-4c2a-8d25-6859177770dd\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 31, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"c1876839-d7c3-41b4-95f9-26e67e13ccb5\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"Water as a source of life\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"4ef44ce4-f3bf-411b-aa86-fb6f6fee86bd\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>In arid regions, water is the most valuable resource, above anything  else. For these regions, we\\u2019ve develop a unique water-saving growing  system. It does not use any fossil water sources, and it saves more than  95% of water compared to open field agriculture, as well as more than  70% compared to currently available greenhouse systems.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"0c04c046-1ae9-45bf-b750-288b044067c3\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"A model for sustainable arid food production\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"7baffddb-7f68-4ae5-a54d-fd924a1e2ae0\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Serenity Farms gets its electrical power from the sun, and recycles its  waste water to extract as much valuable nutrients as possible. For this  we include innovative growing systems, saline growth, algae, and  aquaculture.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"65c1bdde-e6ed-4e75-a1f7-629d19ecbb33\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 32, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"82e288be-fbdf-493d-8f21-7e6951d994d8\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"Growing into the future\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"b5d12daa-943d-4e0c-a76b-c384080b355a\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>The roadmap for Serenity Farms aims towards towards self sustained  growing in energy, water sourcing, and waste processing. Additional  areas of ambition are sourcing of sustainable nutrient sources, and CO2  injection. \\u00a0Serenity Farms produces organically as much as possible,  closing its biomaterial loops, and being as circular as possible in its  operations, including packaging.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"17d25adb-946d-40a3-af81-95fe3775f501\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 33, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"48ef92ac-a9a8-4049-9cfa-077b2a79cef2\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"Simulating the desert\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"d75e7806-1cac-4b49-a4e6-10ef60b03d5d\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>To meet the complex technical challenge of feasibly producing food at a  profitable rate in difficult environments, Except created an advanced  simulation and modelling tool. It integrates high-end technological  solutions for climate control, water treatment, energy production, and  nutrient mixing technology making it fully adaptable to different  environments. The tool enables testing assumptions and the different  tradeoffs between technologies, resources, land use, logistics and  operational decisions, as well as profitability.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"c87606ff-448d-41f0-8d18-88a5660d3e62\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"Serenity Farms in a nutshell;\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"0a0f09c5-76ef-4a33-8cf0-f9cb0fe680c1\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<ul><li> Food security for local population by reliably producing healthy fresh food of consistent quality year round<br/> </li><li>A boost to local economy by creating employment for a range  of skilled and educated workers, from senior management, human  resources, and harvesting to research, administration, hospitality, and  packaging<br/> </li><li>Knowledge development industry on sustainable food production in arid regions<br/> </li><li>Education and training, capacity development, and an improvement to human capital<br/> </li><li>Significant reduction in the use of water compared to open field agriculture<br/> </li><li>CO2 and air pollution savings by eliminating imports and  associated freight for fresh food supplies and by producing its own  electricity<br/> </li></ul>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"6958d295-392c-4da3-b2d6-41ee984d1aa9\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Serenity  Farms initiates a new food production industry for the future. It  provides fresh food to the region, long term high quality jobs,  education, and economic growth. It increases national food production  and food security, in addition to reducing environmental footprint and  resource use.</p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"fab34911-30ec-4bfc-9dbf-4182005b046f\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 29, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"58e62fc3-a585-4c89-83bb-e61bd2cb06ac\"}]','[{\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Serenity Farms produces and delivers food in regions that have limited  or no access to fresh produce. These regions currently import food,  usually through air freight, which has a large environmental impact,  reduces quality and availability, and creates inconsistent supply. For  example, in Saudi Arabia, where we are looking to develop a Serenity  Farm, over 80% of all fresh food is imported. </p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"00f89ee7-36e2-4c63-a096-bf60766e45ae\"}, {\"value\": {\"image\": 30, \"attribution\": \"\", \"caption\": \"\"}, \"type\": \"image_block\", \"id\": \"389ad0f5-a760-4c12-9661-d694f485250b\"}, {\"value\": {\"heading_text\": \"Food for the desert\", \"size\": \"h3\"}, \"type\": \"heading_block\", \"id\": \"6c795431-31c3-4279-ab8e-3aafcc714055\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"<p>Humanity faces a global challenge of feeding 9 billion people  sustainably in 2050.\\u00a0 It is estimated that in today\\u2019s world nearly 1  billion people are malnourished. </p>\"}, \"type\": \"paragraph_block\", \"id\": \"63e8d972-f243-489c-a86f-e564bf4d4b10\"}, {\"value\": {\"text\": \"Taking into account a growing population and shifting diets, the world will need to produce 69% more food calories in 2050 than we did in 2006.\", \"attribute_name\": \"World Resources Institute\"}, \"type\": \"block_quote\", \"id\": \"22b3b799-682d-4e9b-869b-c5043e20cc60\"},