ch better ways, working with supply chains and learning from nature.','The industrial revolution left us with a radically different world, with its benefits and problems. Today, we find that the supply chains we rely on for vital resources are ancient, inefficient, and fragile. Luckily, there are plenty of options to start producing our food, products, and energy in much better ways, working with supply chains and learning from nature.',74,'Enabling regenerative food, products & logistics'),(28,'Training & Coaching','Training & Coaching','Training & Coaching','In-company, Open registration, Train-the-trainer','In-company, Open registration, Train-the-trainer','In-company, Open registration, Train-the-trainer','purple','We offer a variety of training for professionals to learn and practice integrated sustainability. We host regular open registration courses, offer tailor made in-company trajectories, as well as industry specific train-the-trainer programs. all programs are based on the Symbiosis in Development (SiD) framework.','We offer a variety of training for professionals to learn and practice integrated sustainability. We host regular open registration courses, offer tailor made in-company trajectories, as well as industry specific train-the-trainer programs. all programs are based on the Symbiosis in Development (SiD) framework.','We offer a variety of training for professionals to learn and practice integrated sustainability. We host regular open registration courses, offer tailor made in-company trajectories, as well as industry specific train-the-trainer programs. all programs are based on the Symbiosis in Development (SiD) framework.',73,'In-company, Open registration, Train-the-trainer');
