aph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Jon Woning  is a biotechnologist by choice, and curious by nature. He has earned  his beekeeping certificate, and has recently adopted his first hive.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"bacbeeef-4b99-4fc6-a70e-e55d3b54ba70\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}]\", \"owner\": 1, \"show_in_menus\": false, \"path_to_thumbnail\": null, \"live_revision\": null, \"author\": null, \"live\": true, \"hero_title_nl\": null, \"service\": 25, \"highlight\": true, \"seo_title\": \"\", \"linked_articles\": [], \"url_path_en\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/knowledge/keeping-our-bees/\", \"title_nl\": null, \"last_published_at\": null, \"date_published\": null}',NULL,31,1),(50,0,'2019-09-14 15:23:16.612872','{\"slug_nl\": null, \"numchild\": 0, \"depth\": 4, \"hero_title_en\": \"Keeping Our Bees\", \"hero_title\": \"Keeping Our Bees\", \"downloads\": [], \"navbar_transparent\": true, \"hero_subtitle\": \"Celebrate World Bee Day 2019 with Except Biotechnologist Jon Woning\", \"locked\": false, \"seo_title_en\": null, \"body\": \"[{\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cBees play a huge role in the systematic cultivation of fruit, as the main pollinators in orchards,\\\\u201d says Jon. \\\\u201cTogether with other pollination dependent crops, this represents a rough third of all our food on the planet.\\\\u201d While bees are the public image of cross-pollination, this critical natural process does not belong to the bees alone. A large number of insect species, including bumblebees, wasps, and flies, hold together our ecosystems with cross-pollination. These insects are a necessity for over 70% of wild species of plants, and a third of the world\\\\u2019s agricultural crops.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"6e892272-37a5-4dfa-8cbf-bd8440eda06e\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The FAO estimates that between $235 and $577 billion (U.S.) worth of annual global food production relies on the direct contribution of pollinators, and over 4,000 different species of bees contribute to pollination. For a country like the UK, the value of the bees&#x27; services were estimated at \\\\u00a3200m a year. The retail value of what they pollinate was valued closer to \\\\u00a31bn (UK National Audit Office, 2007).</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"bed9ca79-2324-405b-9842-4bb6ad0b7fc5\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The honeybee is by far the most protected species, as they provide a source of economic value. The decline in honeybees signifies a terrifying trend for other insect species, that do not receive this protection. Insect populations in Europe have dwindled over 90% over the last two centuries, due to human interference.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"38c32f21-dc44-4a71-81de-49c9337f7cc8\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cWorld Bee Day is a great opportunity to give these critical critters the attention they deserve,\\\\u201d says Jon. \\\\u201cBees are truly fascinating creatures, with complex societies and social structures that we as humans can aspire to. Their function as guardians of flora-rich ecosystems, ensures their place and purpose in this world.\\\\u201d</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"6628899e-089b-4721-9214-fde3147178aa\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>There are around 20,000 species of bees, only one of which is the common honeybee. They come in many colours. Most bees don&#x27;t dance, and, only a few species make honey.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"1b3c96a9-8f71-4e83-bc4e-ba1b2f924f21\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cWe have to recognise these insects\\\\u2019 pivotal role in the natural world. It\\\\u2019s critical to regard their well-being as a vital indicator for the health of our ecosystems. When our protected bees fall we will follow, given time.\\\\u201d</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"30e865d2-0ebc-4f97-bce5-87f284b7b40b\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Important insect populations also suffer at the hands of our domestic efforts. Many gardens today are boarded up or turned into stone patches. Together with the huge grasslands which are used for agriculture \\\\u2013 but are deserts to bees \\\\u2013 our own backyards make up part of these shrinking ecosystems. As a result, the bees\\\\u2019 natural territory, and their ability to spread from ecosystem to ecosystem has been severely limited.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"2d02a719-2512-4499-bbe3-73cb18fc7f06\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cBecause of this fact, a lot of flowering flora, including those in your gardens, have seen a decline. Without bees and other pollinators, the world is literally a less colourful place. Individuals have the ability to make a large positive impact on the decline of bee species and the ecosystems that support them. Please help the bees around you, and replace some of the stone and grass with some (native) flowers!\\\\u201d</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"89360b4d-2cb8-4be6-b35b-e465cb6ecb9b\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>If you want to find out more on World Bee Day, Jon recommends the following further reading and watching materials:</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"858e0036-da10-41e4-b24d-184dc99fde37\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<ul><li>More Than Honey (2012) is a film on the different beekeeping practices in the world, and the status of their existence.<br/></li><li>For the Dutch among us who enjoy a well illustrated piece of educational reading, check out Het Complete Bijenboek (ISBN 978 94 6143 159 2).<br/></li><li>If you want to find out more about why we need bees, read this report by the NRDC on how Nature\\\\u2019s Tiny Workers Put Food on Our Tables.<br/></li><li>Or check in with your local beekeeper society. These organisation often provide courses or other material on the subject of bees, as well being an excellent source of fresh locally sourced honey (definitely worth a try).<br/></li></ul>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"77ecc3bb-2ca9-4a03-86dc-6a55905c9595\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Jon Woning is a biotechnologist by choice, and curious by nature. He has earned his beekeeping certificate, and has recently adopted his first hive.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"bacbeeef-4b99-4fc6-a70e-e55d3b54ba70\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}]\", \"title\": \"Keeping Our Bees\", \"search_description\": \"\", \"intro_en\": \"Today, following the recent UN report outlining the devastating degradation of our planet\\u2019s natural biodiversity, is World Bee Day. To celebrate these magnificent creatures which are vital for the preservation of earth\\u2019s ecological balance, we asked Jon Woning, Except\\u2019s resident biotechnologist and bee enthusiast, to talk us through the importance of cross-pollination in our society.\", \"body_nl\": \"[]\", \"go_live_at\": null, \"first_published_at\": \"2019-09-14T15:22:49.682Z\", \"intro_nl\": \"\", \"url_path_nl\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/knowledge/keeping-our-bees/\", \"title_en\": \"Keeping Our Bees\", \"navbar_inverted\": true, \"expire_at\": null, \"seo_title_nl\": null, \"url_path\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/knowledge/keeping-our-bees/\", \"draft_title\": \"Keeping Our Bees\", \"has_unpublished_changes\": false, \"intro\": \"Today, following the recent UN report outlining the devastating degradation of our planet\\u2019s natural biodiversity, is World Bee Day. To celebrate these magnificent creatures which are vital for the preservation of earth\\u2019s ecological balance, we asked Jon Woning, Except\\u2019s resident biotechnologist and bee enthusiast, to talk us th