t protected species, as they provide a source of economic value. The decline in honeybees signifies a terrifying trend for other insect species, that do not receive this protection. Insect populations in Europe have dwindled over 90% over the last two centuries, due to human interference.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"38c32f21-dc44-4a71-81de-49c9337f7cc8\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cWorld Bee Day is a great opportunity to give these critical critters the attention they deserve,\\\\u201d says Jon. \\\\u201cBees are truly fascinating creatures, with complex societies and social structures that we as humans can aspire to. Their function as guardians of flora-rich ecosystems, ensures their place and purpose in this world.\\\\u201d</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"6628899e-089b-4721-9214-fde3147178aa\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>There are around 20,000 species of bees, only one of which is the common honeybee. They come in many colours. Most bees don&#x27;t dance, and, only a few species make honey.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"1b3c96a9-8f71-4e83-bc4e-ba1b2f924f21\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cWe have to recognise these insects\\\\u2019 pivotal role in the natural world. It\\\\u2019s critical to regard their well-being as a vital indicator for the health of our ecosystems. When our protected bees fall we will follow, given time.\\\\u201d</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"30e865d2-0ebc-4f97-bce5-87f284b7b40b\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Important insect populations also suffer at the hands of our domestic efforts. Many gardens today are boarded up or turned into stone patches. Together with the huge grasslands which are used for agriculture \\\\u2013 but are deserts to bees \\\\u2013 our own backyards make up part of these shrinking ecosystems. As a result, the bees\\\\u2019 natural territory, and their ability to spread from ecosystem to ecosystem has been severely limited.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"2d02a719-2512-4499-bbe3-73cb18fc7f06\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cBecause of this fact, a lot of flowering flora, including those in your gardens, have seen a decline. Without bees and other pollinators, the world is literally a less colourful place. Individuals have the ability to make a large positive impact on the decline of bee species and the ecosystems that support them. Please help the bees around you, and replace some of the stone and grass with some (native) flowers!\\\\u201d</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"89360b4d-2cb8-4be6-b35b-e465cb6ecb9b\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>If you want to find out more on World Bee Day, Jon recommends the following further reading and watching materials:</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"858e0036-da10-41e4-b24d-184dc99fde37\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<ul><li>More Than Honey (2012) is a film on the different beekeeping practices in the world, and the status of their existence.<br/></li><li>For the Dutch among us who enjoy a well illustrated piece of educational reading, check out Het Complete Bijenboek (ISBN 978 94 6143 159 2).<br/></li><li>If you want to find out more about why we need bees, read this report by the NRDC on how Nature\\\\u2019s Tiny Workers Put Food on Our Tables.<br/></li><li>Or check in with your local beekeeper society. These organisation often provide courses or other material on the subject of bees, as well being an excellent source of fresh locally sourced honey (definitely worth a try).<br/></li></ul>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"77ecc3bb-2ca9-4a03-86dc-6a55905c9595\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Jon Woning is a biotechnologist by choice, and curious by nature. He has earned his beekeeping certificate, and has recently adopted his first hive.</p>\\\"}, \\\"id\\\": \\\"bacbeeef-4b99-4fc6-a70e-e55d3b54ba70\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\"}]\", \"owner\": 1, \"show_in_menus\": false, \"path_to_thumbnail\": null, \"live_revision\": 49, \"author\": null, \"live\": true, \"hero_title_nl\": null, \"service\": 25, \"highlight\": true, \"seo_title\": \"\", \"linked_articles\": [], \"url_path_en\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/knowledge/keeping-our-bees/\", \"title_nl\": null, \"last_published_at\": \"2019-09-14T15:22:49.682Z\", \"date_published\": \"2019-05-28\"}',NULL,31,1),(51,0,'2019-09-14 15:33:59.993279','{\"service\": 22, \"downloads\": [{\"name\": \"Systemic value of a true\", \"path_to_thumbnail\": null, \"file\": \"natural_capital_v4_tb_med.jpg\", \"page\": 32, \"name_nl\": null, \"pk\": 1, \"name_en\": \"Systemic value of a true\"}], \"linked_articles\": [], \"intro\": \"The land we grow our food on, water that flows through it, animals and plants living in this environment, and the oceans - the birthplace of life. This, and more, is our natural capital; the value represented by our ecosystems, species, and everything in between that we rely on to persist on this planet. All of our natural systems are declining fast, and this threatens our future. It puts at risk the continuation of any business with a complex supply chain, and jeopardizes the resource availability of any nation.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Natural Capital (NC) movement attempts to halt and reverse this trend by embedding the value of natural systems into economic systems. This article talks about how Natural Capital works, what the pitfalls and opportunities of such a system are, and how we can accelerate implementation in government and business.\", \"url_path\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/knowledge/natural-capital-new-innovation-strategies/\", \"hero_title_en\": \"Natural Capital & new innovation strategies\", \"hero_subtitle\": \"How to accelerate natural value systems\", \"owner\": 1, \"body_en\": \"[{\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>While there is debate about NC as a concept, it is one of the few  answers we have. Organizations around the world are moving to implement  it because of rapidly increasing ecological destruction. But there is  much to be done, and progress is slow. There are opportunities to  accelerate and improve Natural Capital based on innovative systems  solutions for business and policy alike. Solutions that not only  conserve nature but puts the front runners of NC in a position of  significant advantage, both in business and policy.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"44844abd-304f-443a-b0a0-9a5a8c03099b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Why Natural Capital?\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"42d49fe1-6274-4ce4-934c-a21216a18cb4\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The concept of Natural Capital has been around for more than a century  and is not without controversy. Debate about its ethical foundations has  been going on for decades, raising ethical questions without clear  answers, but the global decline of nature pressures us for action.  Nature currently has limited economic value, causing it to be regularly  sacrificed. This &#x27;<a href=\\\\\\\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tragedy_of_the_commons\\\\\\\">tragedy of the commons</a>&#x27; plagues conservation efforts and the debate has delayed solutions resulting in preventable losses. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"8b0622e9-b348-4307-b347-f742acd03f52\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>At the <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.naturalcapitalforum.com/\\\\\\\">2013 World Forum on Natural Capital</a>  in Edinburgh, organized by the Scottish Wildlife Trust, most policy and  business representatives agreed it\\\\u2019s time to take action, putting the  ethical discussion to the background. Barry Gardiner, UK shadow minister  for the environment, said it most poignantly: </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"6445f2db-65fa-422c-8cab-6f971157663f\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"We use nature because it gives us value, and we destroy it because it\'s free. Nature should be given the rightful value it deserves, it\\\\u2019s the only real way we can safeguard our natural resources for the future.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"25bf9a23-4462-4b29-b801-826714dc752d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Because NC is one of the few tools that allows direct action to be  taken, the message is to implement it as fast as we can. How can we do  this? The challenge can be summarized as follows; what mechanisms can we  use to make natural capital work, how to value nature in all its  facets, and how to create an advantage for policy and business for rapid  implementation.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"fb383a1c-da95-4a41-bc8a-34b1dcf28072\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"What mechanisms make Natural Capital work?\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"03beb8bc-624e-483e-948b-618ab82f2548\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The solution supported by the largest NGO&#x27;s introduces national NC  profit and loss balance sheets in each country and company, and tracks  this balance as is done with finance. These balance sheets express  Natural Capital both in terms of quantity and quality of resources  (amounts of forests, water, biodiversity, etc), and, where possible, as  currency. For every asset that disappears from the balance sheet,  something else needs to be brought back. This functions to increase  awareness and transparency about the state of our natural resources, and  improves their management. When successful, Natural Capital Accounting  (NCA) injects a balancing system for our planet\\\\u2019s physical limits to  growth into an economy currently aimed at capitalizing on limitless  growth.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"f33f290d-04e2-437c-9335-69640548cf9c\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Implementing Natural Capital is not without risk, as demonstrated by the  carbon credit scheme that often creates perverse incentives, shifting  damage from one place to another due to incomplete valuation. To prevent  this, NCA needs to take into account the full spectrum of value we  recognise today, and leave room for values that appear in the future.  Values that cannot be expressed in a monetary equivalent need to appear  on the balance sheets in their qualitative form. It will not be possible  to account for all value, but this should not hold us back. As  Professor Dieter Helm explained at the forum in Edinburgh:</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"d7d5232c-44e1-4e4e-b6c8-4de45911e028\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"We do not need to be entirely correct in our assessment of Natural Capital. Even if we\'re only 80% or even 50% in the ballpark, that\\\\u2019s at least better than the value of zero we have currently. We need to act, now, to prevent further losses to an already marginalized system, regardless of not being able to accurately value Natural Capital.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"80319f74-f791-4f63-8f44-60c6b4a9dd4f\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 24, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"37660d11-4b32-4f6b-833b-32d0112f3fdd\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"How do we value nature?\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"0f230716-89e4-4588-96e4-683f31f73e47\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>This is undoubtedly the greatest challenge of Natural Capital as a  concept. What value does a tree have? Ask a hundred scientists and  economists and you will get a hundred different answers. In order for NC  to work, we need to agree on a basis of valuation. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"7d39d443-f8f6-48c8-8bfb-ecd3b149fba9\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>A tree is worth more than just the price of its wood, as it provides a  home to many animals, it acts as shade in summer, it buffers and filters  rainwater, it cleans the air, and it also supplies a number of other  ecosystem services. It may also be valuable in other terms, for example  culturally, and for its role in the ecosystem as a whole. Therefore, the  value of a tree in its entirety isn\\\\u2019t the same as the price for its  wood in the store, and can be expressed in a different manner, for  example in liters of water buffered and filtered, its contribution to  biodiversity and well being, and so on.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c4e1f866-2b30-41c9-99e5-ceec887ab075\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Quite a few studies have attempted to account for some of these values and converted them into currency. Research conducted by <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19755530\\\\\\\">Johnson and Wardle</a>  gave the Canadian Boreal forest a value of US$ 3.7 trillion for all of  its ecosystem services and carbon sequestration. Another study from 1997  by <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.uvm.edu/giee/publications/Nature_Paper.pdf\\\\\\\">Costanza et. al</a>  put a pricetag of US$ 33 trillion on the world\\\\u2019s biosphere\\\\u2019s ecosystem  services. These and other studies give starting points for value  estimation, while there are certainly large gaps to cover. To find and  fill these gaps, a more inclusive framework to assess value is  necessary.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"3196c1d5-81c9-43a9-a69c-5c52ba55a68f\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"SiD as a structure for value\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"4daf9370-e2af-4d85-81cc-af7399bd2023\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The <a href=\\\\\\\"http://except.nl/en/articles/148-symbiosis-in-development-sid\\\\\\\">Symbiosis in Development (SiD)</a>  systems analysis framework is such a tool. It can be used to assess the  full spectrum of value for any given subject, including the relational  values of the system as a whole. Its flexible structure allows room for  future discovery while providing clarity to start valuing with limited  insight today.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"49929fcc-4759-4707-88d3-fbbfe78d41a2\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Using SiD the value of the tree can be seen on three &#x27;scales&#x27;: the  object (direct physical) value, the value of its network (services and  relations), and its systemic value as a whole. The first being the  easiest to assess, and the last the hardest but having the most impact.  Combining these three scales results in a estimation of the tree\\\\u2019s  Natural Capital value.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"5948f13c-d421-4462-88df-393f1a9a4704\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 25, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"This diagram is a simplified example of the structure of SiD\\\\u2019s value assessment when applied to a tree.\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"4edcea54-2eea-4e68-ac8d-14ae528bc5f6\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Using SiD, there are opportunities for other values to join the party,  such as transparency, diversity, health, and wellbeing. SiD reserves  room for these values, allowing them to be slotted in once research  makes them available. Because it is a universal framework, it works for  other measurements as well, allowing it to be inclusive of other  movements such as social justice or poverty alleviation and stand  stronger together. This flexibility prevents the system becoming  solidified once adopted, preventing perverse incentives that occur when  real value and value in the system are dissonant (an issue that plagues  carbon trading). Tracking the flexibility of the Natural Capital system  is therefore essential.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"607c9f04-4c81-41e1-a83c-52a4891eda08\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Giving Natural Capital teeth\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"846aaf8a-c7dc-40e7-b5cb-a40fccd5c298\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>There are frameworks for valuation, which can be filled in using  existing research. Then incentives are needed for organizations to  implement them. Using systemic innovation strategies, the most effective  approaches can be explored. As a trial, a small interdisciplinary team  at Except, a sustainability strategy firm, held a short systems  exploration session and came up with a few approaches. It was discovered  that effective solutions are those that make Natural Capital a base  economic requirement for growth, rooting it into the core of the  economy.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"2638841e-e68a-416f-90a0-5672ec143e45\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>One approach is to create a secondary currency backed by Natural Capital  rather than gold. This means Natural Capital is not expressed in  Dollars, Euros or Yen, but in its own currency, for example called the  GreenBack. This currency is purely digital, relying on similar  technology as BitCoin, and coupled to the balance sheets of nations,  capturing both qualitative and quantitative values in separate  indicators. When demand for this GreenBack goes up, a direct increase in  demand for Natural Capital results. This creates a natural marketplace  where the only way to grow wealth is to grow Natural Capital. This  currency thus couples economic growth to its necessary precursor: the  resources our planet needs to sustain economic growth.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"0d7672b6-a04a-4941-b9c3-b015c0a37b5b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Solutions like these accelerate the implementation of Natural Capital,  but both business and government have their own challenges. What are the  opportunities for countries and companies to implement NC?</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"99aa3be5-b09a-499a-be5d-e435a5d3765d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 26, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"8db23d3e-2c4f-4b55-921c-d09f0279d6f5\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Opportunities to accelerate NCA in policy\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"357fcd21-8c87-473e-b88d-cbb815a04bdb\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"In 50 years\\\\u2019 time we will look back and say that our governments were economically illiterate. They simply did not understand the true value of the most important service providers on our planet. We will marvel that they failed to capture and make explicit the value of Natural Capital and ecosystem services in their national accounts.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"Barry Gardiner, MP\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"522a3a0c-b111-4de8-bfcb-908cbac23600\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Several projects researching the role of NC in policy are underway, for  example TEEB, a global research project through the European Union. But  progress is slow, hampered by lack of oversight, tools for valuation,  accessible knowledge databases, and stakeholder awareness. These  challenges can be more effectively solved with innovative  systems-thinking than traditional approaches, saving resources and time.  And time is of the essence here. One way to speed up the process is to  apply distributed innovation mechanisms, such as crowd-solutioning and  serious gaming. These approaches have managed to resolve in weeks highly  complex problems such as <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/sarikabansal/2011/09/28/crowdsourcing-gamers-solve-protein/\\\\\\\">unraveling the secrets of protein folding</a>,  which previously took teams of scientists many years. If strategies  such as these were to be applied to the issues that hold back Natural  Capital, solutions could be implemented at a much faster rate, and  Natural Capital Accounting could be in place in many countries within  the next decade.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"db76a7be-8278-4031-891e-ee4205d576da\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>But, Natural Capital can only be effective if it&#x27;s adopted voluntarily  by both government and business. Enforcement takes too long and the  stick causes loopholes, while the carrot accelerates the process. Why  would a profit driven company be interested to implement and invest in  Natural Capital?</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"df6328ea-9e72-4f61-a80c-ed285ee7ebea\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 27, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c0cc39ac-a508-4a53-85e4-fce207d37b4d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Advantages of embedding NCA in business\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"220236c4-6cef-408a-91bb-03c72738d037\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>At first sight, business may not seem to have an interest in Natural  Capital or Natural Capital Accounting, as it does not directly lead to  profit. But there are several reasons why this is not only advantageous,  but critical to the survival of business today and tomorrow.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"293c87b5-bf70-442b-a1ab-1c92c3171b6b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>In complex supply chains, change comes quickly and strikes hard. Most  companies rely on one or more natural resources somewhere in their  supply chain, yet may not be aware of where and how. Tracking NC is  essential to ensure continued business in the short and long term. If a  sizeable business is not tracking this, it is not conducting proper risk  management.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"e24cd87c-5d9b-423e-8e7a-d4509f48b5f0\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>In addition, business can use NC to find valuable ecosystems services  while improving CSR performance at the same time. For example, companies  have found bio-based alternatives to artificial or fossil resources  that save money and provide long term sourcing security.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"06dc9eab-847a-49c4-90b7-2df3eaf3af6d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>It is also good for businesses to be ahead of the curve when it comes to  issues that governments will eventually demand. Waiting to be forced  into something through regulation risks costly solutions being enforced.  Also, being one of the first to start NC accounting has its perks. It  allows an organization to shape the conversation, be more opportunistic  with investments, and get public recognition for leading the good fight.  This has been shown by Puma, which started publishing the first  Environmental Profit &amp; Loss Account (EPLA) under direction of their  holding company Kering, and already tracked 145 million in environmental  impacts in <a href=\\\\\\\"http://about.puma.com/wp-content/themes/aboutPUMA_theme/financial-report/pdf/EPL080212final.pdf\\\\\\\">2010</a>. This resulted in positive press globally, several companies following suit, and creating a catch-up game for everyone else.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"310f8b67-938a-4e49-af63-27b8199340e7\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Lastly, insurance companies are becoming interested in Natural Capital  Accounting. After all, threats to resources that a company relies on are  threats to the company, and insurance will go up or become unavailable.  And it is not just insurance firms. Standards &amp; Poor\\\\u2019s, one of the  Big-Three credit rating firms, is investigating Natural Capital  Accounting as a new input for the same reasons, directly affecting a  company\\\\u2019s credit rating. That should be reason enough for the big  players out there to start moving.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"a57c8c76-ad5b-4bba-a76e-b035900396e7\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h4\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Making it happen\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"e3db8b60-8a68-4e70-81ca-d919666bc819\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>There are many reasons to start implementing NC as fast as possible. A  structured and systemic approach is critical to make it succeed. This is  why solutions like SiD exist. We call on the front runners of NC to aim  higher and gain the advantage of using innovative systems tools and  implementation strategies, such as natural currencies, crowd-solutioning  and systemic risk assessment. The front runners in policy, business,  and NGOs should be brought together to collectively accelerate the  process and support each other. It is in our joint interest to do so. We  have the tools, expertise, and manpower to do this, so let\\\\u2019s make  Natural Capital accounting a reality within a few years, and gain huge  benefits for each organization and society alike.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"b0a5e7ce-8c2c-4788-9303-191c3e01f344\\\"}]\", \"hero_title_nl\": null, \"navbar_inverted\": true, \"body_nl\": \"[]\", \"slug\": \"natural-capital-new-innovation-strategies\", \"navbar_transparent\": true, \"linked_projects\": [], \"expire_at\": null, \"go_live_at\": null, \"search_description_en\": \"\", \"intro_en\": \"The land we grow our food on, water that flows through it, animals and plants living in this environment, and the oceans - the birthplace of life. This, and more, is our natural capital; the value represented by our ecosystems, species, and everything in between that we rely on to persist on this planet. All of our natural systems are declining fast, and this threatens our future. It puts at risk the continuation of any business with a complex supply chain, and jeopardizes the resource availability of any nation.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Natural Capital (NC) movement attempts to halt and reverse this trend by embedding the value of natural systems into economic systems. This article talks about how Natural Capital works, what the pitfalls and opportunities of such a system are, and how we can accelerate implementation in government and business.\", \"title_en\": \"Natural Capital & new innovation strategies\", \"seo_title_en\": null, \"expired\": false, \"search_description\": \"\", \"hero_title\": \"Natural Capital & new innovation strategies\", \"show_in_menus\": false, \"hero_subtitle_en\": \"How to accelerate natural value systems\", \"live\": true, \"latest_revision_created_at\": null, \"highlight\": true, \"title_nl\": null, \"title\": \"Natural Capital & new innovation strategies\", \"seo_title\": \"\", \"url_path_nl\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/knowledge/natural-capital-new-innovation-strategies/\", \"first_published_at\": null, \"path\": \"0001000100020002\", \"slug_nl\": null, \"top_images\": [{\"sort_order\": 0, \"image\": 23, \"pk\": 2, \"page\": 32}], \"date_published\": null, \"content_type\": 30, \"author\": null, \"numchild\": 0, \"path_to_thumbnail\": null, \"has_unpublished_changes\": false, \"locked\": false, \"depth\": 4, \"live_revision\": null, \"last_published_at\": null, \"pk\": 32, \"search_description_nl\": \"\", \"draft_title\": \"Natural Capital & new innovation strategies\", \"hero_subtitle_nl\": null, \"body\": \"[{\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>While there is debate about NC as a concept, it is one of the few  answers we have. Organizations around the world are moving to implement  it because of rapidly increasing ecological destruction. But there is  much to be done, and progress is slow. There are opportunities to  accelerate and improve Natural Capital based on innovative systems  solutions for business and policy alike. Solutions that not only  conserve nature but puts the front runners of NC in a position of  significant advantage, both in business and policy.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"26ce1837-7447-4641-b85f-0bc719cfd3de\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Why Natural Capital?\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"57ceb175-6167-4021-963c-2c7fb9caaac8\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The concept of Natural Capital has been around for more than a century  and is not without controversy. Debate about its ethical foundations has  been going on for decades, raising ethical questions without clear  answers, but the global decline of nature pressures us for action.  Nature currently has limited economic value, causing it to be regularly  sacrificed. This &#x27;<a href=\\\\\\\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tragedy_of_the_commons\\\\\\\">tragedy of the commons</a>&#x27; plagues conservation efforts and the debate has delayed solutions resulting in preventable losses. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"869376e0-8cca-4673-a05c-faea044722ce\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>At the <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.naturalcapitalforum.com/\\\\\\\">2013 World Forum on Natural Capital</a>  in Edinburgh, organized by the Scottish Wildlife Trust, most policy and  business representatives agreed it\\\\u2019s time to take action, putting the  ethical discussion to the background. Barry Gardiner, UK shadow minister  for the environment, said it most poignantly: </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"1413dba5-bb80-40c2-a4d7-5aca992e5b94\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"We use nature because it gives us value, and we destroy it because it\'s free. Nature should be given the rightful value it deserves, it\\\\u2019s the only real way we can safeguard our natural resources for the future.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"a01824e4-cd4a-44b1-a199-b5e7559acb64\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Because NC is one of the few tools that allows direct action to be  taken, the message is to implement it as fast as we can. How can we do  this? The challenge can be summarized as follows; what mechanisms can we  use to make natural capital work, how to value nature in all its  facets, and how to create an advantage for policy and business for rapid  implementation.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"53163c18-3ef9-4876-beb9-6d8ae6ad9867\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"What mechanisms make Natural Capital work?\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c58d4a5d-1824-4381-b414-f16ef5402cdc\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The solution supported by the largest NGO&#x27;s introduces national NC  profit and loss balance sheets in each country and company, and tracks  this balance as is done with finance. These balance sheets express  Natural Capital both in terms of quantity and quality of resources  (amounts of forests, water, biodiversity, etc), and, where possible, as  currency. For every asset that disappears from the balance sheet,  something else needs to be brought back. This functions to increase  awareness and transparency about the state of our natural resources, and  improves their management. When successful, Natural Capital Accounting  (NCA) injects a balancing system for our planet\\\\u2019s physical limits to  growth into an economy currently aimed at capitalizing on limitless  growth.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"5b6fd022-8d27-4843-993f-774a00dd4c4b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Implementing Natural Capital is not without risk, as demonstrated by the  carbon credit scheme that often creates perverse incentives, shifting  damage from one place to another due to incomplete valuation. To prevent  this, NCA needs to take into account the full spectrum of value we  recognise today, and leave room for values that appear in the future.  Values that cannot be expressed in a monetary equivalent need to appear  on the balance sheets in their qualitative form. It will not be possible  to account for all value, but this should not hold us back. As  Professor Dieter Helm explained at the forum in Edinburgh:</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"dd60bad3-adc5-4c72-901e-0b6f64b3394b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"We do not need to be entirely correct in our assessment of Natural Capital. Even if we\'re only 80% or even 50% in the ballpark, that\\\\u2019s at least better than the value of zero we have currently. We need to act, now, to prevent further losses to an already marginalized system, regardless of not being able to accurately value Natural Capital.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"31ad3a69-fb86-405f-bc20-c749696a7734\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 24, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"263a0868-3165-493f-9252-c21855ca0f3b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"How do we value nature?\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"86be4164-1ddd-4bb1-b62a-59c503b24b8b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>This is undoubtedly the greatest challenge of Natural Capital as a  concept. What value does a tree have? Ask a hundred scientists and  economists and you will get a hundred different answers. In order for NC  to work, we need to agree on a basis of valuation. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"d21775ae-c06f-42da-8c4d-f29215f9c8d0\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>A tree is worth more than just the price of its wood, as it provides a  home to many animals, it acts as shade in summer, it buffers and filters  rainwater, it cleans the air, and it also supplies a number of other  ecosystem services. It may also be valuable in other terms, for example  culturally, and for its role in the ecosystem as a whole. Therefore, the  value of a tree in its entirety isn\\\\u2019t the same as the price for its  wood in the store, and can be expressed in a different manner, for  example in liters of water buffered and filtered, its contribution to  biodiversity and well being, and so on.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"7ca8be35-4095-411b-8665-f3f907977ba2\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Quite a few studies have attempted to account for some of these values and converted them into currency. Research conducted by <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19755530\\\\\\\">Johnson and Wardle</a>  gave the Canadian Boreal forest a value of US$ 3.7 trillion for all of  its ecosystem services and carbon sequestration. Another study from 1997  by <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.uvm.edu/giee/publications/Nature_Paper.pdf\\\\\\\">Costanza et. al</a>  put a pricetag of US$ 33 trillion on the world\\\\u2019s biosphere\\\\u2019s ecosystem  services. These and other studies give starting points for value  estimation, while there are certainly large gaps to cover. To find and  fill these gaps, a more inclusive framework to assess value is  necessary.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"2bbd4fdd-111a-461d-b813-5babdc124daf\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"SiD as a structure for value\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"253767d4-f570-4fd6-8835-fbc6f2019cf5\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The <a href=\\\\\\\"http://except.nl/en/articles/148-symbiosis-in-development-sid\\\\\\\">Symbiosis in Development (SiD)</a>  systems analysis framework is such a tool. It can be used to assess the  full spectrum of value for any given subject, including the relational  values of the system as a whole. Its flexible structure allows room for  future discovery while providing clarity to start valuing with limited  insight today.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"0444299c-51da-4a90-bcac-8ea785a56388\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Using SiD the value of the tree can be seen on three &#x27;scales&#x27;: the  object (direct physical) value, the value of its network (services and  relations), and its systemic value as a whole. The first being the  easiest to assess, and the last the hardest but having the most impact.  Combining these three scales results in a estimation of the tree\\\\u2019s  Natural Capital value.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"1ba15b52-eec3-4fe9-a240-9e381a0f2b5c\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 25, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"This diagram is a simplified example of the structure of SiD\\\\u2019s value assessment when applied to a tree.\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"0bb08c30-7fd9-423e-8ded-cbfde4ef27c5\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Using SiD, there are opportunities for other values to join the party,  such as transparency, diversity, health, and wellbeing. SiD reserves  room for these values, allowing them to be slotted in once research  makes them available. Because it is a universal framework, it works for  other measurements as well, allowing it to be inclusive of other  movements such as social justice or poverty alleviation and stand  stronger together. This flexibility prevents the system becoming  solidified once adopted, preventing perverse incentives that occur when  real value and value in the system are dissonant (an issue that plagues  carbon trading). Tracking the flexibility of the Natural Capital system  is therefore essential.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"67c1246c-65c7-475b-bec4-846a3e90ca34\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Giving Natural Capital teeth\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"d2be3465-e00a-4a86-8d9b-d616e342a8b0\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>There are frameworks for valuation, which can be filled in using  existing research. Then incentives are needed for organizations to  implement them. Using systemic innovation strategies, the most effective  approaches can be explored. As a trial, a small interdisciplinary team  at Except, a sustainability strategy firm, held a short systems  exploration session and came up with a few approaches. It was discovered  that effective solutions are those that make Natural Capital a base  economic requirement for growth, rooting it into the core of the  economy.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"25db1c44-f9e6-45ec-99fd-246ee5b5c298\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>One approach is to create a secondary currency backed by Natural Capital  rather than gold. This means Natural Capital is not expressed in  Dollars, Euros or Yen, but in its own currency, for example called the  GreenBack. This currency is purely digital, relying on similar  technology as BitCoin, and coupled to the balance sheets of nations,  capturing both qualitative and quantitative values in separate  indicators. When demand for this GreenBack goes up, a direct increase in  demand for Natural Capital results. This creates a natural marketplace  where the only way to grow wealth is to grow Natural Capital. This  currency thus couples economic growth to its necessary precursor: the  resources our planet needs to sustain economic growth.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"31d2ade3-15ae-4d87-9e28-6c2135d7ea6f\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Solutions like these accelerate the implementation of Natural Capital,  but both business and government have their own challenges. What are the  opportunities for countries and companies to implement NC?</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"38f2ef1d-1250-48ec-9c12-3ef210cf7215\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 26, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"462d708d-1bd1-4e65-b67f-d010f87315c7\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Opportunities to accelerate NCA in policy\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"76857587-8aab-4ee9-8579-e83b31a4b4fa\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"In 50 years\\\\u2019 time we will look back and say that our governments were economically illiterate. They simply did not understand the true value of the most important service providers on our planet. We will marvel that they failed to capture and make explicit the value of Natural Capital and ecosystem services in their national accounts.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"Barry Gardiner, MP\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c71e762b-e9ef-49e0-8753-1e2247e120f2\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Several projects researching the role of NC in policy are underway, for  example TEEB, a global research project through the European Union. But  progress is slow, hampered by lack of oversight, tools for valuation,  accessible knowledge databases, and stakeholder awareness. These  challenges can be more effectively solved with innovative  systems-thinking than traditional approaches, saving resources and time.  And time is of the essence here. One way to speed up the process is to  apply distributed innovation mechanisms, such as crowd-solutioning and  serious gaming. These approaches have managed to resolve in weeks highly  complex problems such as <a href=\\\\\\\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/sarikabansal/2011/09/28/crowdsourcing-gamers-solve-protein/\\\\\\\">unraveling the secrets of protein folding</a>,  which previously took teams of scientists many years. If strategies  such as these were to be applied to the issues that hold back Natural  Capital, solutions could be implemented at a much faster rate, and  Natural Capital Accounting could be in place in many countries within  the next decade.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"58fb5281-a279-411e-994c-7e3c7d2f5a4f\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>But, Natural Capital can only be effective if it&#x27;s adopted voluntarily  by both government and business. Enforcement takes too long and the  stick causes loopholes, while the carrot accelerates the process. Why  would a profit driven company be interested to implement and invest in  Natural Capital?</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"43aa2d4f-30b6-46fd-866c-fd3949bde160\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 27, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c1efccd2-8e95-4d6c-aa27-0f0372e3f5f9\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Advantages of embedding NCA in business\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"5a650eb2-c709-44f9-b62d-fd0bbef62a32\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>At first sight, business may not seem to have an interest in Natural  Capital or Natural Capital Accounting, as it does not directly lead to  profit. But there are several reasons why this is not only advantageous,  but critical to the survival of business today and tomorrow.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"b0d1ce9e-3991-400b-984e-d5b54cfd78c0\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>In complex supply chains, change comes quickly and strikes hard. Most  companies rely on one or more natural resources somewhere in their  supply chain, yet may not be aware of where and how. Tracking NC is  essential to ensure continued business in the short and long term. If a  sizeable business is not tracking this, it is not conducting proper risk  management.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"b0a4e6be-06ff-4266-916c-416f8ac4a928\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>In addition, business can use NC to find valuable ecosystems services  while improving CSR performance at the same time. For example, companies  have found bio-based alternatives to artificial or fossil resources  that save money and provide long term sourcing security.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"fb26df4c-4f70-44fe-8e30-0521f81b843c\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>It is also good for businesses to be ahead of the curve when it comes to  issues that governments will eventually demand. Waiting to be forced  into something through regulation risks costly solutions being enforced.  Also, being one of the first to start NC accounting has its perks. It  allows an organization to shape the conversation, be more opportunistic  with investments, and get public recognition for leading the good fight.  This has been shown by Puma, which started publishing the first  Environmental Profit &amp; Loss Account (EPLA) under direction of their  holding company Kering, and already tracked 145 million in environmental  impacts in <a href=\\\\\\\"http://about.puma.com/wp-content/themes/aboutPUMA_theme/financial-report/pdf/EPL080212final.pdf\\\\\\\">2010</a>. This resulted in positive press globally, several companies following suit, and creating a catch-up game for everyone else.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"2376df57-d6f8-4786-99a3-560d87def985\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Lastly, insurance companies are becoming interested in Natural Capital  Accounting. After all, threats to resources that a company relies on are  threats to the company, and insurance will go up or become unavailable.  And it is not just insurance firms. Standards &amp; Poor\\\\u2019s, one of the  Big-Three credit rating firms, is investigating Natural Capital  Accounting as a new input for the same reasons, directly affecting a  company\\\\u2019s credit rating. That should be reason enough for the big  players out there to start moving.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"a6aa0d8c-4918-475c-9b06-a23a6c34e670\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h4\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Making it happen\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"ba08898e-0052-49e1-a050-978d10d70c65\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>There are many reasons to start implementing NC as fast as possible. A  structured and systemic approach is critical to make it succeed. This is  why solutions like SiD exist. We call on the front runners of NC to aim  higher and gain the advantage of using innovative systems tools and  implementation strategies, such as natural currencies, crowd-solutioning  and systemic risk assessment. The front runners in policy, business,  and NGOs should be brought together to collectively accelerate the  process and support each other. It is in our joint interest to do so. We  have the tools, expertise, and manpower to do this, so let\\\\u2019s make  Natural Capital accounting a reality within a few years, and gain huge  benefits for each organization and society alike.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"f9bde6ae-10f9-4f7d-8092-d7168cae1c58\\\"}]\", \"intro_nl\": \"\", \"url_path_en\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/knowledge/natural-capital-new-innovation-strategies/\", \"slug_en\": \"natural-capital-new-innovation-strategies\", \"seo_title_nl\": null}',NULL,32,1),(52,0,'2019-09-14 15:41:21.305684','{\"service\": 25, \"project_partners\": [], \"downloads\": [{\"name\": \"SF Logo\", \"path_to_thumbnail\": null, \"file\": \"SF-LogoBRASHuse_web_679x494.jpg\", \"page\": 33, \"name_nl\": null, \"pk\": 1, \"name_en\": \"SF Logo\"}], \"linked_articles\": [], \"intro\": \"Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates. The core of Serenity Farms is a repeatable \\u2018stamp\\u2019 design, producing the annual fresh food nutrition needs for over 60.000 people. It sources and treats water from renewable sources exclusively such as seawater, and is fully powered by the sun. This way we produce healthy, consistent, high quality fresh produce for people that currently have no direct food source, and greatly reduce the food\'s carbon footprint.\", \"url_path\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/projects/serenity-farms/\", \"hero_title_en\": \"Serenity Farms\", \"external_members\": [], \"hero_subtitle\": \"Sustainable food production in arid regions\", \"owner\": 1, \"body_en\": \"[{\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Serenity Farms produces and delivers food in regions that have limited  or no access to fresh produce. These regions currently import food,  usually through air freight, which has a large environmental impact,  reduces quality and availability, and creates inconsistent supply. For  example, in Saudi Arabia, where we are looking to develop a Serenity  Farm, over 80% of all fresh food is imported. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"00f89ee7-36e2-4c63-a096-bf60766e45ae\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 30, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"389ad0f5-a760-4c12-9661-d694f485250b\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Food for the desert\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"6c795431-31c3-4279-ab8e-3aafcc714055\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Humanity faces a global challenge of feeding 9 billion people  sustainably in 2050.\\\\u00a0 It is estimated that in today\\\\u2019s world nearly 1  billion people are malnourished. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"63e8d972-f243-489c-a86f-e564bf4d4b10\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"Taking into account a growing population and shifting diets, the world will need to produce 69% more food calories in 2050 than we did in 2006.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"World Resources Institute\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"22b3b799-682d-4e9b-869b-c5043e20cc60\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>A changing climate, on top of dwindling resources needed for  agriculture, complicates our collective mandate to grow more food in  time. Food security and effects on national autonomy are of significant  concern to many countries, especially those with a low domestic food  production capacity. This is especially true for arid regions, where  often no fresh produce source is available at all. To make local  sustainable food production in the desert a reality,\\\\u00a0 we initiated the  Serenity Farms project.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"243ee737-203e-45ae-b70a-f1763fcc3ffd\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"The ultimate goal of farming is not the growing of crops, but the cultivation and perfection of human beings.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"Masanobu Fukuoka, The One-Straw Revolution\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"e8c5bee9-e99c-4c2a-8d25-6859177770dd\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 31, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c1876839-d7c3-41b4-95f9-26e67e13ccb5\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Water as a source of life\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"4ef44ce4-f3bf-411b-aa86-fb6f6fee86bd\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>In arid regions, water is the most valuable resource, above anything  else. For these regions, we\\\\u2019ve develop a unique water-saving growing  system. It does not use any fossil water sources, and it saves more than  95% of water compared to open field agriculture, as well as more than  70% compared to currently available greenhouse systems.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"0c04c046-1ae9-45bf-b750-288b044067c3\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"A model for sustainable arid food production\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"7baffddb-7f68-4ae5-a54d-fd924a1e2ae0\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Serenity Farms gets its electrical power from the sun, and recycles its  waste water to extract as much valuable nutrients as possible. For this  we include innovative growing systems, saline growth, algae, and  aquaculture.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"65c1bdde-e6ed-4e75-a1f7-629d19ecbb33\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 32, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"82e288be-fbdf-493d-8f21-7e6951d994d8\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Growing into the future\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"b5d12daa-943d-4e0c-a76b-c384080b355a\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The roadmap for Serenity Farms aims towards towards self sustained  growing in energy, water sourcing, and waste processing. Additional  areas of ambition are sourcing of sustainable nutrient sources, and CO2  injection. \\\\u00a0Serenity Farms produces organically as much as possible,  closing its biomaterial loops, and being as circular as possible in its  operations, including packaging.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"17d25adb-946d-40a3-af81-95fe3775f501\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 33, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"48ef92ac-a9a8-4049-9cfa-077b2a79cef2\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Simulating the desert\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"d75e7806-1cac-4b49-a4e6-10ef60b03d5d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>To meet the complex technical challenge of feasibly producing food at a  profitable rate in difficult environments, Except created an advanced  simulation and modelling tool. It integrates high-end technological  solutions for climate control, water treatment, energy production, and  nutrient mixing technology making it fully adaptable to different  environments. The tool enables testing assumptions and the different  tradeoffs between technologies, resources, land use, logistics and  operational decisions, as well as profitability.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c87606ff-448d-41f0-8d18-88a5660d3e62\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Serenity Farms in a nutshell;\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"0a0f09c5-76ef-4a33-8cf0-f9cb0fe680c1\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<ul><li> Food security for local population by reliably producing healthy fresh food of consistent quality year round<br/> </li><li>A boost to local economy by creating employment for a range  of skilled and educated workers, from senior management, human  resources, and harvesting to research, administration, hospitality, and  packaging<br/> </li><li>Knowledge development industry on sustainable food production in arid regions<br/> </li><li>Education and training, capacity development, and an improvement to human capital<br/> </li><li>Significant reduction in the use of water compared to open field agriculture<br/> </li><li>CO2 and air pollution savings by eliminating imports and  associated freight for fresh food supplies and by producing its own  electricity<br/> </li></ul>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"6958d295-392c-4da3-b2d6-41ee984d1aa9\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Serenity  Farms initiates a new food production industry for the future. It  provides fresh food to the region, long term high quality jobs,  education, and economic growth. It increases national food production  and food security, in addition to reducing environmental footprint and  resource use.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"fab34911-30ec-4bfc-9dbf-4182005b046f\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 29, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"58e62fc3-a585-4c89-83bb-e61bd2cb06ac\\\"}]\", \"hero_title_nl\": null, \"navbar_inverted\": true, \"body_nl\": \"[]\", \"slug\": \"serenity-farms\", \"navbar_transparent\": true, \"linked_projects\": [], \"expire_at\": null, \"go_live_at\": null, \"search_description_en\": \"\", \"intro_en\": \"Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates. The core of Serenity Farms is a repeatable \\u2018stamp\\u2019 design, producing the annual fresh food nutrition needs for over 60.000 people. It sources and treats water from renewable sources exclusively such as seawater, and is fully powered by the sun. This way we produce healthy, consistent, high quality fresh produce for people that currently have no direct food source, and greatly reduce the food\'s carbon footprint.\", \"title_en\": \"Serenity Farms\", \"seo_title_en\": null, \"expired\": false, \"search_description\": \"\", \"hero_title\": \"Serenity Farms\", \"show_in_menus\": false, \"hero_subtitle_en\": \"Sustainable food production in arid regions\", \"live\": true, \"latest_revision_created_at\": null, \"numchild\": 0, \"highlight\": true, \"title_nl\": null, \"title\": \"Serenity Farms\", \"seo_title\": \"\", \"url_path_nl\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/projects/serenity-farms/\", \"summary_nl\": null, \"first_published_at\": null, \"path\": \"0001000100030001\", \"slug_nl\": null, \"top_images\": [{\"sort_order\": 0, \"image\": 28, \"pk\": 1, \"page\": 33}, {\"sort_order\": 1, \"image\": 29, \"pk\": 2, \"page\": 33}], \"team_members\": [], \"date_published\": \"2018-10-16\", \"content_type\": 49, \"author\": null, \"summary\": \"Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates.\", \"path_to_thumbnail\": null, \"has_unpublished_changes\": false, \"locked\": false, \"depth\": 4, \"live_revision\": null, \"last_published_at\": null, \"pk\": 33, \"search_description_nl\": \"\", \"draft_title\": \"Serenity Farms\", \"summary_en\": \"Serenity Farms is a concept for a sustainable 30 ha greenhouse facility for profitable food production in arid climates.\", \"hero_subtitle_nl\": null, \"body\": \"[{\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Serenity Farms produces and delivers food in regions that have limited  or no access to fresh produce. These regions currently import food,  usually through air freight, which has a large environmental impact,  reduces quality and availability, and creates inconsistent supply. For  example, in Saudi Arabia, where we are looking to develop a Serenity  Farm, over 80% of all fresh food is imported. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"30e47357-0467-4cd4-be1b-2c1bc79df12e\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 30, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"59d17d29-c050-4186-b246-ccd59e089499\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Food for the desert\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"6b758e62-8e29-4ee5-adfe-d5c5849acae1\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Humanity faces a global challenge of feeding 9 billion people  sustainably in 2050.\\\\u00a0 It is estimated that in today\\\\u2019s world nearly 1  billion people are malnourished. </p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"8ba45f4f-5f7a-4ef7-b47c-a2717ae36ad1\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"Taking into account a growing population and shifting diets, the world will need to produce 69% more food calories in 2050 than we did in 2006.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"World Resources Institute\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"ef49c113-0611-4112-8763-b3a8760ee9f6\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>A changing climate, on top of dwindling resources needed for  agriculture, complicates our collective mandate to grow more food in  time. Food security and effects on national autonomy are of significant  concern to many countries, especially those with a low domestic food  production capacity. This is especially true for arid regions, where  often no fresh produce source is available at all. To make local  sustainable food production in the desert a reality,\\\\u00a0 we initiated the  Serenity Farms project.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"d474948b-3618-4cc2-b067-7a7b48c81a28\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"The ultimate goal of farming is not the growing of crops, but the cultivation and perfection of human beings.\\\", \\\"attribute_name\\\": \\\"Masanobu Fukuoka, The One-Straw Revolution\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"block_quote\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"1ab0910a-c7a6-4385-b9ca-643dff928f5f\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 31, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"6f8c3396-7fe8-4bf1-bb87-dea2bafc540c\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Water as a source of life\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"4e01fc34-1557-4491-a4a1-4fc5a617d70c\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>In arid regions, water is the most valuable resource, above anything  else. For these regions, we\\\\u2019ve develop a unique water-saving growing  system. It does not use any fossil water sources, and it saves more than  95% of water compared to open field agriculture, as well as more than  70% compared to currently available greenhouse systems.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"d96cee45-38ec-4b12-b719-70627f37725e\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"A model for sustainable arid food production\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"4c4f204a-13b0-4f32-9881-e5288e67f46d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Serenity Farms gets its electrical power from the sun, and recycles its  waste water to extract as much valuable nutrients as possible. For this  we include innovative growing systems, saline growth, algae, and  aquaculture.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"430c7277-c3bf-411c-93dd-c617267e824d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 32, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"c3d10f01-4b6c-459f-8050-c105b37123ef\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Growing into the future\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"2ab914ea-17a7-4c89-9bc8-85d401d055b4\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The roadmap for Serenity Farms aims towards towards self sustained  growing in energy, water sourcing, and waste processing. Additional  areas of ambition are sourcing of sustainable nutrient sources, and CO2  injection. \\\\u00a0Serenity Farms produces organically as much as possible,  closing its biomaterial loops, and being as circular as possible in its  operations, including packaging.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"fcf1fbe0-d818-4d1b-b67c-8e59b6c28f1d\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 33, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"eeddf37e-1140-415e-afa0-e4508a065c83\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Simulating the desert\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"dffea6fe-2d2a-46f7-bb91-354bc06215fb\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>To meet the complex technical challenge of feasibly producing food at a  profitable rate in difficult environments, Except created an advanced  simulation and modelling tool. It integrates high-end technological  solutions for climate control, water treatment, energy production, and  nutrient mixing technology making it fully adaptable to different  environments. The tool enables testing assumptions and the different  tradeoffs between technologies, resources, land use, logistics and  operational decisions, as well as profitability.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"af69efd9-2fd2-4fee-b85a-c260c2784c68\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"size\\\": \\\"h3\\\", \\\"heading_text\\\": \\\"Serenity Farms in a nutshell;\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"heading_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"3286ddd5-9e7d-4b02-9892-1b600d5e2325\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<ul><li> Food security for local population by reliably producing healthy fresh food of consistent quality year round<br/> </li><li>A boost to local economy by creating employment for a range  of skilled and educated workers, from senior management, human  resources, and harvesting to research, administration, hospitality, and  packaging<br/> </li><li>Knowledge development industry on sustainable food production in arid regions<br/> </li><li>Education and training, capacity development, and an improvement to human capital<br/> </li><li>Significant reduction in the use of water compared to open field agriculture<br/> </li><li>CO2 and air pollution savings by eliminating imports and  associated freight for fresh food supplies and by producing its own  electricity<br/> </li></ul>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"b49d4562-b852-46ca-8eff-8d0d817f9682\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Serenity  Farms initiates a new food production industry for the future. It  provides fresh food to the region, long term high quality jobs,  education, and economic growth. It increases national food production  and food security, in addition to reducing environmental footprint and  resource use.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"221bd3f5-814a-445d-9470-f19d325903a7\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 29, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"b7e1d87f-43f9-46b1-8c9a-f5f3236f0dfd\\\"}]\", \"intro_nl\": \"\", \"url_path_en\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/projects/serenity-farms/\", \"slug_en\": \"serenity-farms\", \"seo_title_nl\": null}',NULL,33,1),(53,0,'2019-09-14 15:47:02.778575','{\"service\": 17, \"project_partners\": [], \"downloads\": [], \"linked_articles\": [], \"intro\": \"Historic sites struggle to find business models that protect and optimize their cultural heritage in a rapidly changing world. The owners of the medieval castle of Sterkenburg in Driebergen decided to take up this challenge, looking for new ways to reignite its economic and social value. They engaged a multidisciplinary group of sustainability experts from Except Integrated Sustainability, who developed a special program to help historic sites unearth their opportunities. The resulting roadmap delivers concrete, immediate cost savings in the short term, and new ways for the castle to play a role in both today\\u2019s, and tomorrow\\u2019s society.\", \"url_path\": \"/except-integrated-sustainability/projects/future-sterkenburg/\", \"hero_title_en\": \"The Future of Sterkenburg\", \"external_members\": [], \"hero_subtitle\": \"Medieval castle Sterkenburg innovates a new future\", \"owner\": 1, \"body_en\": \"[{\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>Dating back to at least 1261, the Sterkenburg castle lies 20 km outside  the city of Utrecht and is one of the few privately managed estates left  in the country. As owners, the van Helsdingen family take good care of  the estate, respecting its original function as a private household.The  family is no stranger to the challenge faced by several owners of listed  heritage buildings in the Netherlands - high maintenance costs and  limited capacity for revenue creation.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"798dea4f-b88d-4b13-a6a0-ee4624fd50b3\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 36, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"d532cab2-e891-44ea-a8fb-1ac58753d442\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>How do we turn cultural heritage sites back into properties that are  valued in today\\\\u2019s fast changing society? At Except we developed an  approach to design roadmaps to tackle complex problems. In February of  this year, a team of experts from Except gathered with the owners on the  estate. Together, we co-created a comprehensive program that sets a new  future for the castle.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"431a4445-6e61-4e36-9826-0fb2d3f6e89e\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The roadmap consists of short- and long- term items in the areas of  energy consumption, user experience, and society. The outcome reduces  operational costs, enhances the business model, and reconnects the  function of the castle with broader societal issues via an engaging  event program, the \\\\u201cClub of Sterkenburg\\\\u201d. The Club nurtures national and  international policy-making fora on the topics of cultural heritage and  sustainability, engaging and linking both business and government.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"7d2c999b-9b5e-4f94-8728-6e574c5a5de2\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"image\\\": 37, \\\"attribution\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"caption\\\": \\\"\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"image_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"17e82c6a-6e11-4274-b107-8f59c0fbdd48\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The short-term roadmap saves on operational costs through significant  improvements in energy usage, including lighting, appliances, heating,  and hot water. \\\\u201cThe predicted reduction of electricity consumption  ensures a complete return of investment in less than a year\\\\u201d says Jacob  Verhaart, Head of Science at Except. All short term measures can be  easily implemented by the family themselves.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"cd7290df-6184-405b-9232-6e4949bf7a98\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>The business model capitalizes on unexpressed potentials of the estate,  and sets a new paradigm for the future of listed heritage buildings in  the Netherlands and globally.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"a06d5889-0b24-40e0-b255-f9a7d0a08d27\\\"}, {\\\"value\\\": {\\\"text\\\": \\\"<p>\\\\u201cI found it deeply inspiring to imagine this castle not only as a place  that takes, but that also gives back to society\\\\u201d says Maurits van  Helsdingen. \\\\u201cWe have been imagining the future of Sterkenburg for 15  years\\\\u201d, concludes his father Jelle. \\\\u201cAfter a long time, we discussed the  idea from truly comprehensive perspectives. I am sure this is the start  of a bright future for Sterkenburg Castle\\\\u201d.</p>\\\"}, \\\"type\\\": \\\"paragraph_block\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"66fa8e6d-6d6e-4db7-93b0-dc6911f65edc\\\"}